            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="451" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/11–948: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ward</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mukden</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-09">November 9,
                            1948</date>.<lb/>[Received November 9—12:43 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>539. <hi rend="italic">Sheng Tang Shih Pao</hi> today states North China People’s
                    Government established September 20 with Tung Pi-wu [as] Chairman and Pu I-po,
                    Lan Kung-wu and Yang Hsiu-feng [as] first, second and third vice chairman
                    respectively. Other heads of Government Lan Kung-wu, Minister Interior; Chao
                    Chieh-fu, Minister Education; Jung Tse-ho, Minister Finance; Yao I-lin, Minister
                    Industry and Commerce; Sung Shao-wen, Minister Agriculture; Huang Ching,
                    Minister State Enterprises; Wu Ching-tien, Minister Communications; Yin
                    Hsih-peng, Minister Health; Hsu Chien-kuo, Minister Security; Hsieh Chueh-tsai,
                    Minister Justice. November 2 will henceforth be celebrated in northeast as
                    Victory Day.</p>
                <p>Sent Nanking 672, repeated Department 539, Tientsin 179, Peiping 264.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ward</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
